Â Our daughter was born with a condition called congenital femoral deficiency. Â She's had 4 surgeries and another big one planned in May which will leave her unable to walk for 6 months. She has come across obstacles that have caused problems but we always find a way to overcome it. Â We've always told her she can do anything she wants as long as she sets her mind to do it. This ad made me think of Tom Dempsey.  Dempsey was born with a deformed foot.  He eventually used that foot to kick the longest field goal in NFL history, a record that stood for many years until it was broken recently.  Could you imagine the parents holding their newborn baby with a deformed foot and being told that their baby would use that foot to kick the longest field goal in NFL history?  That is incredible to me.
